HEADWORD: Dominus
<hw>Dom"i*nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Domini</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., master. See
<er>Dame</er>.]</ety> <def>Master; sir; -- a title of respect formerly
applied to a knight or a clergyman, and sometimes to the lord of a
manor.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

